/*
 * CompileAndReport - COM/OLE-drivable "compile & validate" entry point for the Equation block
 * -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 * Proposed addition to the Value library Equation block.
 *
 * Purpose
 *   Let an external OLE/COM automation client (e.g. a Python or C# host driving
 *   ExtendSim.Application) compile the block's current equation and read back a
 *   pass/fail verdict WITHOUT any modal dialog and WITHOUT running the model.
 *
 * How a client uses it
 *   1. SetDialogVariable(blockNum, "EQ_EquationText",  <equation text>, 0, 0)
 *   2. SetDialogVariable(blockNum, "CompileAndReport", 1,               0, 0)   // fires this handler
 *   3. Read the verdict:  global0    -> 1 = compiled OK, 0 = compile error
 *                         globalStr0 -> "" on success, else an error indication
 *
 * Why an in-block handler is required
 *   app.Execute() from COM runs in SYSTEM context. From there a client cannot call the
 *   equation compiler, nor read the block-private compiled-code array (EQ_CompiledEquation).
 *   A dialog-item handler, by contrast, runs in BLOCK context and can do both. Setting the
 *   CompileAndReport dialog variable from COM fires this handler, bridging the two worlds.
 *
 * Requires
 *   A dialog item named "CompileAndReport" (checkbox) so that setting it from COM fires
 *   this "on CompileAndReport" handler.
 */
on CompileAndReport
{
	integer compileError;

	// Translate EQ_EquationText into ExtendSim's internal form (fills EQ_TranslatedEquationText).
	EQ_TranslateEquation();

	// Compile SILENTLY: this primitive returns a nonzero error code on bad syntax and does
	// NOT pop a UserError dialog, unlike the interactive EQ_Compile() path (which also calls
	// AbortAllSims()). It is the same silent primitive EQ_Compile() itself uses at OpenModel
	// time. See the KNOWN ISSUE in README.md: this call currently HANGS on invalid equations
	// when invoked outside a running simulation.
	compileError = EquationCompileDynamicVariablesSilent("iVars_Values", "oVars_Values",
		EQ_TranslatedEquationText, EQ_CompiledEquation, EQUATION_TAB_ORDER);

	if (compileError == 0)
	{
		global0 = 1;		// ok: equation compiled cleanly
		globalStr0 = "";	// no error
	}
	else
	{
		global0 = 0;		// compile / syntax error
		globalStr0 = "Equation compile error code " + compileError;
	}
}//on CompileAndReport
